{'author': 'Felipe Soares <felipe.staypuff@gmail.com>',
 'description': 'Original Checkmk plugin (through v1.0.2) created by '
                'wellingtonsilva67@gmail.com. This plugin uses agent_modbus '
                'v2.1 as its data source, developed by Vincent Tacquet '
                '(https://github.com/vtacquet/agent_modbus). Set the Server '
                'Address, port, slave and the registers you want to query from '
                'the device. Consult the device documentation to find out '
                'which registers you want and test them via command line '
                'before configuring the services in the web interface. '
                'Version 1.0.7 fixes multiple Modbus slaves on one host for '
                'real: Checkmk only ever keeps one data source per special '
                'agent name per host, so yielding one command per slave '
                '(1.0.4-1.0.6) only ever ran the last slave - all Modbus '
                'slaves configured in the rule are now queried by a single '
                'agent_modbus invocation that loops over them internally and '
                'tolerates individual slave failures. Version 1.0.4 changed '
                'the "Check Modbus devices" rule so a single rule can '
                'configure several Modbus slaves. Version 1.0.3 fixed the '
                'value parser and added a "Modbus register value scaling" '
                'rule to display/graph values with decimal places. This '
                'Checkmk plugin (rulesets, server_side_calls and check logic) '
                'was adapted and is maintained by Felipe Soares '
                '(https://github.com/felipesoaresti/).',
